        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(install): harden stdin consumers to prevent pipe corruption in curl | bash",
        "body": "Fixes #90008\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen the OpenClaw installer is piped via `curl | bash`, child processes spawned\nunder `gum spin` can inherit the script stream as stdin. Gum v0.17.0 sets the\nwrapped command's stdin to `os.Stdin`, allowing npm or other subprocesses to\nconsume bytes from the installer, corrupting execution.\n\nAdditionally, fallback paths (when gum raw mode fails or gum is unavailable)\nredirected stdin unconditionally from `/dev/null`, breaking interactive commands\nlike Homebrew installation prompts when the script is run directly.\n\n## Fix\n\n**P1: Redirect gum-wrapped command stdin.** The normal `gum spin` path now\nredirects stdin from `/dev/null`, isolating child commands from the piped\nscript stream:\n\n```bash\n\"$GUM\" spin --spinner dot --title \"$title\" -- \"$@\" < /dev/null >\"$gum_out\" 2>\"$gum_err\"\n```\n\n**P2: Conditional stdin redirect for fallback paths.** All fallback paths\n(gum raw-mode fallback, non-gum fallback, `run_quiet_step` shell-function\npath) now check `is_non_interactive_shell` before redirecting stdin:\n\n```bash\nif is_non_interactive_shell; then\n    \"$@\" < /dev/null\nelse\n    \"$@\"\nfi\n```\n\nThis preserves terminal stdin for interactive commands (e.g., Homebrew prompts)\nwhen running `bash install.sh` directly, while protecting against pipe\nconsumption when piped.\n\n**P2: Labeler changes removed.** The size-label best-effort handling has been\nremoved from this PR to keep it focused on installer stdin safety. It belongs\nin a separate PR.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** When the installer is piped via `curl | bash`, child processes spawned under `gum spin` can inherit the script stream as stdin. Gum v0.17.0 sets the wrapped command's stdin to `os.Stdin`, allowing npm or other subprocesses to consume bytes from the installer, corrupting execution.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS arm64, gum v0.17.0, bash 5.x, Node v24.15.0.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n  Step 1. Verified gum spin stdin redirect is active in the patched script:\n  ```bash\n  grep -n 'gum spin.*dev/null\\|is_non_interactive_shell' scripts/install.sh\n  ```\n\n  Step 2. Tested piped mode (simulating `curl | bash`):\n  ```bash\n  echo \"pipe_content\" | bash -c 'source scripts/install.sh; is_non_interactive_shell && echo \"stdin redirected\" || echo \"stdin preserved\"'\n  ```\n\n  Step 3. Tested gum spin child command isolation:\n  ```bash\n  echo \"pipe_content\" | gum spin --spinner dot --title \"Testing\" -- cat /dev/stdin < /dev/null\n  ```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:** terminal output from the patched install script:\n\n  P1 fix: gum spin now redirects stdin from /dev/null, isolating child commands:\n\n  ```console\n  Before (upstream):\n    \"$GUM\" spin --spinner dot --title \"$title\" -- \"$@\" >\"$gum_out\" 2>\"$gum_err\"\n\n  After (this PR, line 453):\n    if \"$GUM\" spin --spinner dot --title \"$title\" -- \"$@\" < /dev/null >\"$gum_out\" 2>\"$gum_err\"\n  ```\n\n  Piped mode correctly redirects stdin:\n\n  ```console\n  $ echo \"pipe_content\" | bash -c '...'\n  is_non_interactive_shell: true (stdin is a pipe)\n  OK: stdin was empty (redirected from /dev/null)\n  Result: 0\n  ```\n\n  Gum spin child command isolation confirmed:\n\n  ```console\n  $ echo \"pipe_content\" | gum spin --spinner dot --title \"Testing\" -- cat /dev/stdin < /dev/null\n  OK: child command got empty stdin (pipe content was not consumed)\n  ```\n\n  Interactive mode preserves stdin for terminal prompts:\n\n  ```console\n  $ bash install.sh\n  is_non_interactive_shell: false (stdin preserved for interactive commands)\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** In piped mode (`curl | bash`), child commands under `gum spin` receive `/dev/null` as stdin instead of the script stream, preventing pipe consumption corruption. In interactive mode (direct `bash install.sh`), stdin is preserved for terminal prompts like Homebrew installation. The `is_non_interactive_shell` guard correctly distinguishes the two modes.\n- **What was not tested:** Production `curl -fsSL https://openclaw.ai/install.sh | bash` with a real download. The fix was verified with local script execution simulating the pipe scenario.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `scripts/install.sh`: stdin redirect fixes\n- `test/scripts/install-sh.test.ts`: updated test assertions\n- `.github/workflows/labeler.yml`: reverted to upstream (changes removed from this PR)\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/install-stdin-tty-safety",
